    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-01T18:49:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-01T18:49:00-05:00" n="449"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">974.5301/8–151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_AWR1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-01T19:49:00-04:00"
                            >August 1, 1951—7:49 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>178. Re Suez: <persName corresp="#p_SS1">Sarper</persName> gave <persName
                        corresp="#p_RJC1">Ross</persName> today summary long conversation he had
                    with <persName corresp="#p_FBM1">Fawzi</persName> yesterday. <persName
                        corresp="#p_FBM1">Fawzi</persName> gave <persName corresp="#p_SS1"
                        >Sarper</persName> essentially same story he gave <persName
                        corresp="#p_GEA1">Gross</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_RJC1"
                        >Ross</persName> Monday with following significant additions: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_FBM1">Fawzi</persName> very explicitly and
                            categorically said Egypt would not comply with <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                                >SC</gloss> resolution. <persName corresp="#p_SS1">Sarper</persName>
                            thinks this is no bluff and is himself convinced Egyptians will not
                            comply. <persName corresp="#p_FBM1">Fawzi</persName> argued this would
                            be first time Egypt had not complied whereas Israelis had many times
                            failed to comply with <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> resolutions.
                            Moreover, US, UK, Netherlands as parties to dispute would not be
                            entitled to vote; therefore resolution would be illegal.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_FBM1">Fawzi</persName>, re alternative oil
                            refining facilities, spoke of Turkey as well as Egypt and Lebanon as
                            alternative locations. He said setting up of alternative facilities was
                            matter of 3 to 6 months; meanwhile, restrictions would be alleviated. He
                            went further, however, indicating if assurances were forthcoming that
                            alternative facilities would be established Egypt would abolish
                            restrictions forthwith.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Ross gave <persName corresp="#p_SS1">Sarper</persName> full, frank exposé US
                    present attitude and course: (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) Restrictions contrary at
                    least spirit of armistice agreement and obstacle to peace and stability <gloss
                        target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss>; (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) we did not agree
                    argument state war, belligerency; (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) Egypt wrong and
                    objective should be voluntary lifting restrictions soonest. We prepared
                    co-sponsor resolution and working out details with UK and French dels. On
                    arriving at agreed text would of course give to <persName corresp="#p_SS1"
                        >Sarper</persName> (he urged to be given text in time to get instructions;
                    otherwise, no choice but abstain). We also thought we might give text to
                        <persName corresp="#p_FBM1">Fawzi</persName> (and Israelis) as fair warning;
                        <persName corresp="#p_SS1">Sarper</persName> thought this good idea.</p>
                <p>On question of <hi rend="italic">rapporteur</hi>, <persName corresp="#p_SS1"
                        >Sarper</persName> informed UK <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>
                    against, French del favored, US position still reserved. (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CJE1">Coulson</persName> personal view that <hi rend="italic"
                        >rapporteur</hi> idea might well serve useful purpose if time limit one week
                    set.)</p>
                <p>Sarper convinced and strongly expressed view that if solution can be found at all
                    it can only be found outside <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>. Reserved re <hi
                        rend="italic">rapporteur</hi> idea. If function only to report back to
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, no useful purpose. If get matter settled
                    outside council, might be worthwhile. In any case minimum of 2 weeks necessary,
                    taking into account (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) slowness communications between
                    Cairo and Egyptian del here and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) necessity Egypt
                    consult other Arab States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
